              embeddings can be then used for various downstream tasks,
              including clustering, trajectory and pseudotime inference,
              cell-to-cell interaction, etc . Extensive experiments in various
              datasets have been conducted to demonstrate the effectiveness and
              robustness of the proposed conST, achieving up to 10\% improvement
              in clustering ARI in the commonly used benchmark dataset. We also
              show that the learned embedding can be used in complicated
              scenarios, such as predicting cancer progression by analyzing the
              tumour microenvironment and cell-to-cell interaction (CCI) of
