              enhances and decodes spatial transcriptional signals to
              simultaneously achieve spatial domain detection and spatial
              functional genes identification. This novel tunable spatially
              aware strategy of SpaSRL not only balances spatial and
              transcriptional coherence for the two tasks, but also can transfer
              spatial correlation constraint between them based on a unified
              model. Additionally, this joint analysis by SpaSRL deciphers
              accurate and fine-grained tissue structures and ensures the
              effective extraction of biologically informative genes underlying
              spatial architecture. We verified the superiority of SpaSRL on
              spatial domain detection, spatial functional genes identification
              and data denoising using multiple SRT datasets obtained by
              different platforms and tissue sections. Our results illustrate
              SpaSRL's utility in flexible integration of spatial information
              and novel discovery of biological insights from spatial
              transcriptomic datasets. \#\#\# Competing Interest Statement The
              authors have declared no competing interest.",
